tAnnotation.text: Xerox possesses a wealth of experience in the delivery of office services with over 100 contracts in the UK alone managing multi-vendor fleets including the full range of office output devices (faxes, printers, scanners, photocopiers, multi-functional devices) as well as Xerox technology.

hAnnotation.text: Office Services manage all office printing devices - such as printers, copiers, and fax machines - regardless of manufacturer or model.

tAnnotation.text: Xerox will use its experience, tools and methodologies to move COMPANY from its current state to an optimised state via a six month transformation process.

The design of this future state will incorporate long term planning to gradually reduce the number of assets, assign volume to more productive devices and effectively drive up the key user to device ratio.

tAnnotation.text: CentreWare Web Pro is the software tool that provides the core functions for asset reporting and tracking of network connected devices.

For non-networked devices, Xerox will work with site contacts to ensure that all assets are tagged, tracked and updated on the asset register via an established work process in the Welcome and Support Centre.
